    <p><img style="float: right;" src="http://www.ostraining.com/images/drupal/compression.jpg" alt="compression" />It's not unusual for people to tell us that their Drupal sites run slowly.</p>
<p>Part of the reasont that Drupal sites run slowly is that Drupal will load around a dozen CSS and Javascript files by default.</p>
<p>And, if you haven't noticed, each time you add a module to Drupal, there is a chance you are adding even more files.</p>
<p>The image below shows a fairly normal Drupal site and it's loading 31 files!</p>
